One thing that happens, when people get accused of insider trading, is that=
 prosecutors say things like =E2=80=9Cthis guy never traded stock options b=
efore, and then he just happened to buy a lot of options on this stock a we=
ek before it announced a merger.=E2=80=9D Looks suspicious! If you are not =
an active trader, and you do some well-timed trades, juries are more likely=
 to believe that you got an inside tip.
On the other hand if you trade options 100 times a day, and some of them wo=
rk out really well, you can be like =E2=80=9Cwell yes that=E2=80=99s my job=
, I get a lot wrong but I get some big ones right, nothing suspicious about=
 that.=E2=80=9D
I suppose if you get arrested for insider trading, a clever move would be t=
o keep trading those same stocks? =E2=80=9CNo, man, I just innocently trade=
 these stocks all the time, sure it works out sometimes but that=E2=80=99s =
not insider trading, that=E2=80=99s just my deep expertise in the stock.=E2=
=80=9D Not legal advice! Also ideally some of those trades would make money=
.   Anyway:

Joe Lewis, the British billionaire behind one of the world=E2=80=99s bigges=
t investing fortunes, continues to buy and sell stocks at the center of US =
insider-trading allegations against him.
Since being charged by US federal prosecutors in July, the Tavistock Group =
founder has repeatedly traded shares of Mirati Therapeutics Inc., Australia=
n Agricultural Co. and Tango Therapeutics Inc., according to data compiled =
by Bloomberg from regulatory filings. His stakes in those companies =E2=80=
=94 three of the five behind the indictment=E2=80=99s claims =E2=80=94 tota=
l about $540 million.

To be fair, Lewis is not actually accused of=C2=A0insider trading=C2=A0in t=
hose stocks;   he=E2=80=99s accused of=C2=A0tipping=C2=A0other people (=E2=
=80=9Cemployees=C2=A0=E2=80=A6 friends and lovers,=E2=80=9D including two o=
f his private jet pilots) who then traded the stocks. Still =E2=80=9Coh I h=
ave good ideas about those stocks all the time, sometimes I share them with=
 my pilots, but that's never inside information=E2=80=9D is I suppose a def=
ense, so he might as well keep going.

