<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">=E2=80=9CMarket=E2=80=9D</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In theory, every time one company does a merge=
r with another company, or a=C2=A0private equity firm raises a fund from in=
vestors, or a private equity fund borrows money from lenders to do a levera=
ged buyout, the two sides could negotiate all the details of the merger or =
fund or loan from scratch. Sit down and think through the deal from first p=
rinciples: What rights should each side have? Who should have to do what? W=
hat could go wrong, and who should bear the risk of each thing that could g=
o wrong? Negotiate each of these points, and then write a contract in elega=
nt prose that reflects your negotiation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This never really happens.<a class=3D"footnote=
-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; d=
isplay: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Instead the way it works is that the lawyers for one side take ou=
t the contract that they wrote for the last similar deal that they did, and=
 they change the names, and they tweak a few provisions to reflect the curr=
ent situation, and they tweak a few more provisions to be=C2=A0<em>more agg=
ressive</em><em>=C2=A0=E2=80=94</em>=C2=A0to give their client more rights =
or fewer responsibilities, to allocate more risks to the other side =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0and then they send it to the other side. And the lawyers for the o=
ther side mark up the contract to make it more favorable to them (more righ=
ts, fewer responsibilities, less risk), and also to make it look more like =
the last contract=C2=A0<em>they=C2=A0</em>wrote, and they send it back, and=
 they negotiate from there.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In those negotiations, the two sides can make =
several types of arguments. For instance:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some provisions are win-win, so you ca=
n say =E2=80=9Cif you agree to this it will be better for both of us.=E2=80=
=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some provisions are just intui=
tively fair, so you can say =E2=80=9Cit makes no sense for you to allocate =
this risk to us, this is a risk that you should bear,=E2=80=9D and convince=
 the other side of it. (Or: =E2=80=9CIf the contract says this, then that w=
ould allow you to do this crazy unfair thing, and obviously you would never=
 want to do that, so we should change the contract to constrain you in a fa=
ir way.=E2=80=9D)</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Sometimes one si=
de has more negotiating leverage, so it can just say =E2=80=9Cif you don=E2=
=80=99t agree to this we will walk,=E2=80=9D and the other side has to agre=
e.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There=E2=80=99s a certain amoun=
t of arbitrary horse-trading and wearing down of the other side: At 3 a.m.,=
 one side says =E2=80=9Cfine you can have these six points if you give me t=
hose other four points,=E2=80=9D and the other side is like =E2=80=9Cfine w=
hatever let=E2=80=99s be done.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But for many terms in the contract, the=C2=A0<=
em>main=C2=A0</em>argument will be: =E2=80=9CThis term is market.=E2=80=9D<=
a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transp=
arent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a> =E2=80=9CMarket=E2=80=9D means that it is the normal way that these so=
rts of deals are done by sophisticated parties with sophisticated lawyers. =
=E2=80=9CMarket=E2=80=9D is a sort of efficient-market=C2=A0argument. It me=
ans =E2=80=9Ca lot of smart people have argued over this term from first pr=
inciples, they have thought about what is fair and what is in everyone=E2=
=80=99s best interests, and their collective conclusion is that the provisi=
on should be written this way. So who are you to argue for something differ=
ent?=E2=80=9D If there have been 50 private equity leveraged buyouts in the=
 last three years, and 48 of them had a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/33670492.258399/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDctMTEvdGhlLXByaWNlLW9mLW5vdC1idXlpbmctdHdpdHRl=
cj9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMjEyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U=
9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEyMTImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB61e88de1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  cap on damages</a> for non-performan=
ce, then that=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cmarket=E2=80=9D and it is hard =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0not impossible, but hard =E2=80=94=C2=A0for the target to argue that =
there should be no damages cap.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">How do you know what is market? Well, you look=
 at all the previous deals, or as many as you can. Sometimes this is reason=
ably easy: In the US, the terms of some types of deals (public company merg=
ers, initial public offerings, some bond deals) are publicly disclosed with=
 the US Securities and Exchange Commission, so you can just go find them al=
l. (Or all the big ones, or all the ones in your industry, or whatever the =
relevant market is. And obviously you focus on the <em>recent=C2=A0</em>one=
s, since the market evolves.) You have to pay attention to what deals happe=
n, and have someone summarize them, but with a bit of work you can build a =
database, or even keep running track of all the deals in your head I guess.=
<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-6" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: trans=
parent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Or get yourself a large language model and ask it =E2=80=9Cwhat i=
s a standard <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33670=
492.258399/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjIt=
MDctMDkvZWxvbi1zLW91dD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMjEyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWV=
tYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEyMTImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW=
1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB71683ff9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  ordinary course =
of business covenant</a> for a US public company merger these days?=E2=80=
=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Other times it is hard: Many deals are=C2=A0<e=
m>not=C2=A0</em>publicly disclosed, and if you want to know what the standa=
rd terms are for, say, the limited partnership agreement of a new private e=
quity fund, the best way to do that is to have negotiated a ton of private =
equity fund agreements. If you=E2=80=99ve done all of those deals, then you=
 have a database (or all the deal terms in your head), and if the people on=
 the other side haven=E2=80=99t done the deals, then they don=E2=80=99t.=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so you can say =E2=80=9Cthis term is marke=
t=E2=80=9D and they can say =E2=80=9Cno it isn=E2=80=99t=E2=80=9D and you c=
an say =E2=80=9CI have negotiated 100 of these deals and this term is in ev=
ery one of them, how many have you negotiated,=E2=80=9D and they will say =
=E2=80=9Cum, four,=E2=80=9D and they will be ashamed in front of their clie=
nts. You will look wise and experienced, and they will look dumb and unreas=
onable. And you will win the argument. Not always or anything =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0it=E2=80=99s not like anyone is obligated to agree to =E2=80=9Cmarket=E2=
=80=9D terms =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it=E2=80=99s a fairly effective move.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also though if you say =E2=80=9CI have negotia=
ted 100 of these deals and this term is in every one of them,=E2=80=9D and =
they haven=E2=80=99t, and the deals aren=E2=80=99t public, they can=E2=80=
=99t <em>check</em>. If you negotiate all the deals, you can=C2=A0<em>chang=
e=C2=A0</em>what terms are market.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At the Financial Times, Will Louch has a fasci=
nating <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33670492.25=
8399/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvZDg5YjgxMDUtMGI3MS00OWNkLTgzZjctM2=
NlNDhmN2RkYmRk/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd9aac5b2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> profile of Kirkl=
and &amp; Ellis</a>, a US law firm that has become influential and lucrativ=
e by building a strong private equity practice and by being more aggressive=
 and commercial than other law firms. There is a lot about the culture and =
business model of Kirkland, for instance:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Unlike other, stuffier firms, if you are good =
enough you rise through the ranks fast rather than waiting for existing par=
tners to retire or die, he adds. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s run like a business =
and not like a club. A lot of law firms are run like clubs.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another longtime partner says the promotion pr=
ospects are =E2=80=9Cone of the unique things about Kirkland=E2=80=89.=E2=
=80=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89you don=E2=80=99t have to wait until you are 60. =
You can be rewarded really early on and it can give you a sense of energy.=
=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But also, because Kirkland=E2=80=99s private e=
quity practices are so big, they have the ability to move what is market:</=
p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Investors and trade associations are also taki=
ng a closer look at Kirkland=E2=80=99s modus operandi. Because it works on =
so many deals =E2=80=94 it has advised on more fundraisings than any other =
firm in every year since 2008, according to data provider Preqin =E2=80=94 =
it collects reams of data about fees and other terms. The firm invested hea=
vily in using this data to its advantage, even hiring data scientists from =
the University of Chicago to track deal terms.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It uses this data to get better terms for its =
own clients, making life difficult for less well-resourced investors such a=
s public pension plans. =E2=80=9CThey have the largest market share,=E2=80=
=9D says the head of private equity at a large US public pension plan. =E2=
=80=9CThey will pick a few terms each year and insist they are [the] market=
=E2=80=9D,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-co=
lor: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a> rolling them out across most of the private equity funds they advise.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt is one of our selling points,=E2=
=80=9D a person familiar with the firm=E2=80=99s workings says. =E2=80=9COu=
r market knowledge is better than our competitors.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The concentration of market share in the hands=
 of a few large firms, including Simpson Thacher and Proskauer, has attract=
ed criticism from the Institutional Limited Partners Association, a Washing=
ton-based industry body representing private equity investors. In a report =
earlier this year, it highlighted the role that lawyers play in helping fun=
d managers negotiate better terms at the expense of investors.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Investors say they are accused of collusion if=
 they try to band together with peers to get better terms, with Kirkland am=
ong the most aggressive law firms at rebutting any pushback.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One other way to influence what is =E2=80=9Cma=
rket=E2=80=9D=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>to band together with peers, say by bei=
ng the Institutional Limited Partners Association and publishing your own <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33670492.258399/aHR=
0cHM6Ly9pbHBhLm9yZy9tb2RlbC1scGEv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8307faca" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
"> model private equity fund agreement</a>. =E2=80=9CThis term is in the mo=
del agreement so it must be right=E2=80=9D is not quite the same sort of ar=
gument as =E2=80=9Cthis term is market so it must be right,=E2=80=9D but it=
 has some appeal.</p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Lina Khan</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An odd institutional dynamic in US regulation =
right now is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The regulators =E2=80=94=C2=A0at the =
Federal Trade Commission and the Securities and Exchange Commission, at lea=
st =E2=80=94=C2=A0are unusually aggressive about asserting and expanding th=
eir power to regulate.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The courts =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0and in particular the US Supreme Court =E2=80=94=C2=A0are un=
usually skeptical of regulation and willing to cut back the power of regula=
tors.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess that just means =E2=80=9Cthe president=
 is a Democrat and the Supreme Court are mostly Republicans=E2=80=9D? Anywa=
y we have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33670492=
.258399/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDg=
tMjkvZ3JheXNjYWxlLWNhbi1iZS1hLWJpdGNvaW4tZXRmP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEyMTIyM19NT05FWV=
NUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzM=
TIxMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB03af7211" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">  talked</a> a few <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/33670492.258399/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMjgvdGhlLXNlYy1taWdodC1sb3NlLWl0cy1jb3VydHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTI=
xMjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdX=
RtX3Rlcm09MjMxMjEyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
B34795b95" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">  times</a> about how the SEC=E2=80=99s aggressiveness a=
bout expanding its power has clashed with courts that are increasingly aggr=
essive about limiting its power. And here is a <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33670492.258399/aHR0cHM6Ly9ueW1hZy5jb20vaW50ZW=
xsaWdlbmNlci8yMDIzLzEyL2xpbmEta2hhbnMtcm91Z2gteWVhci1ydW5uaW5nLXRoZS1mZWRlc=
mFsLXRyYWRlLWNvbW1pc3Npb24uaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB467876cb" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
"> New York Magazine story about Lina Khan</a>, the chair of the FTC, who h=
as tried to expand the possibilities for US antitrust law=C2=A0and has had =
a string of losses:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A bleaker scenario posited by others is that K=
han=E2=80=99s tenure at the agency could end up playing into the hands of a=
 skeptical Supreme Court, whose conservative majority has made clear that i=
t will push back on what it believes =E2=80=94 fairly or not =E2=80=94 to c=
onstitute overreach on the part of the executive branch. [Former FTC Chair =
William] Kovacic praised Khan for =E2=80=9Cenergizing a new generation of s=
cholars and students=E2=80=9D but noted that =E2=80=9Cthe federal courts se=
em to be edging in the direction of rethinking the scope of the FTC=E2=80=
=99s power =E2=80=94 its decision-making framework, the very constitutional=
ity of how it operates.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The concern is hardly misplaced. The past few =
years have generated several Supreme Court decisions that have curtailed th=
e powers of federal regulators =E2=80=94 including the FTC itself =E2=80=94=
 and made them more vulnerable to legal challenges. The justices recently h=
eard oral argument on a legal challenge to the Securities and Exchange Comm=
ission=E2=80=99s system of in-house courts that could also make matters wor=
se for the FTC, which has a similar system.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t know how much the com=
mission is thinking at the moment about the impact of trying to build a mor=
e expansive program in the face of this gathering judicial storm,=E2=80=9D =
Kovacic wondered. =E2=80=9CDo you realize you could come out of this with a=
 much-diminished agency?=E2=80=9D he asked. =E2=80=9CAnd Congress is not co=
ming to the rescue for you. You could come out of this with an agency that =
is much weaker than the one that you went in with =E2=80=94 permanently wea=
ker.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An FTC that just did traditional FTC stuff mig=
ht still be constrained by courts that are skeptical of regulation, but an =
FTC that tries to expand the possibilities of FTC regulation might end up s=
ignificantly limiting it.</p>
