<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing that happens, when people get accuse=
d of insider trading, is that prosecutors say things like =E2=80=9Cthis guy=
 never traded stock options before, and then he just happened to buy a lot =
of options on this stock a week before it announced a merger.=E2=80=9D Look=
s suspicious! If you are not an active trader, and you do some well-timed t=
rades, juries are more likely to believe that you got an inside tip.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand if you trade options 100 tim=
es a day, and some of them work out really well, you can be like =E2=80=9Cw=
