WZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC4d845f9e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> I wrote</a>: =E2=80=9CLet=
=E2=80=99s say you are a doctor in private practice, you make $500,000 per =
year, and you have $800,000 in the bank. =E2=80=A6 If you sell 10% of your =
practice to a private equity firm, then they will pay you 10% of the presen=
t value of your future earnings. =E2=80=A6 If the private equity firm value=
s your practice at 10 times earnings, then they pay you $500,000 for 10%.=
=E2=80=9D A doctor emailed me to be like =E2=80=9Cis that your sense of the=
 market multiple from recent transactions,=E2=80=9D and I was like =E2=80=
=9Cno, I have no idea, I have never bought or sold a medical practice, 10 i=
s just a convenient round number.=E2=80=9D And he wrote back =E2=80=9Cwell =
it=E2=80=99s pretty accurate.=E2=80=9D Oh boy is this not any sort of marke=
t advice but there you go: 10.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-3" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[3] I say =E2=80=9Cthe prior year=E2=80=9D; as=
 far as I can tell the January 2023/2024 purchase price is 10 times the 202=
2/2023 full-year EBIT, but perhaps the measurement year is slightly differe=
nt. Also really the deal is not that Berkshire buys the last 20% in 2024, b=
ut rather that the sellers have a =E2=80=9CPut Right=E2=80=9D to require Be=
rkshire to buy it in the first 60 days of 2024, or at the beginning of any =
subsequent year (based on the prior year=E2=80=99s EBIT). For simplicity I=
=E2=80=99m assuming that they=E2=80=99d exercise in 2024, and that seems ri=
ght, but in theory they can wait.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-4" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[4] I mean, I=E2=80=99m sure it happens, in th=
e sense that when the first person thought up the first, like, private equi=
ty fund, or carbon offset deal, or whatever, they had to negotiate it from =
scratch. But it doesn=E2=80=99t happen in 2023 in public-company mergers, o=
r private fund raising, or LBO financing, because those are common deals wi=
th a deep reserve of precedents.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-5" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
